  dialogueLines:
  - 'What is there left to say? Like a coward, I have fled and abandoned the last
    memory of Rose. '
  - 'The winds of fate deemed me unworthy of love, and I have now doubly proved my
    unworthiness to steward this child. '
  - "I have traveled this way\u2013 no easy task for my form. If I had wings, I could
    have soared over the obstacles in my way and come to you much earlier. "
  - 'But if that were to be the case, perhaps I would have found you in a state unwilling
    to hear my words, and perhaps if I had not been trialed, I might have found agreement
    in yours. You are loved. '
  - "Rose to you is irreplaceable, that much is clear. For as much love as you have
    for her, the pain of her loss is twofold. If she stood here in your place, would
    she have \u2018abandoned\u2019 this egg as you have claimed to? "
  - 'Preposterous to even suggest such a thing. *Scoff*. My Rose was as caring as
    she was beautiful. Should she be here and I lay dead in the ground, all things
    must be right and just. If she were here, this child would want for nothing and
    not be stranded, but blossom in her sight. How could I leave for a single night? '
  - 'You think quite highly of her. '
  - 'An understatement; I am so drowned in her love that I can find no thought of
    my existence in my mind. '
  - 'Her choice of yourself as a life partner and parent, do you find that decision
    a product of her ignorance or negligence? '
  - 'I resent your questioning; she had been neither. '
  - 'If you should think her wise, then in her wisdom, she found worthiness in you.
    This egg is evidence of that. '
  - 'Despite what you believe yourself to be, she saw in you a capacity for love
    that matched her own. One that she may entrust with her flesh and blood. '
  otherLines:
  - "Your intrusion is unwanted. My plumage is unmatched, yet they cast me out for
    Snake\u2019s lies. I am in no mood for your platitudes. Pester someone else! "
  - "You\u2026 speak as one who has tasted exile. But my paradise of perfection is
    lost forever to the snake. What use is your pity? "
  - "You followed\u2026 even with that cursed thing. Why? "
  - "Your words pierce deeper than any thorn. Isolation has only worsened this self-hatred.
    Leaning on another\u2026 it is not weakness?"
  - "Then I will return with you. This feather proves the snake\u2019s deception\u2014his
    lies that turned my pride to poison. I lashed out because I feared my own incompleteness.
    No more hiding. "
  - "You have shown me what the manuscripts whisper: outer splendor is illusion.
    The soul\u2019s pace is its own paradise. Thank you, wanderer. I am no longer
    banished from myself. "
  - "You have shown me what the manuscripts whisper: outer splendor is illusion.
    The soul\u2019s pace is its own paradise. Thank you, wanderer. I am no longer
    banished from myself. "
